This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on text generation using a generative adversarial network, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel framework for training GANs using maximum likelihood estimation and adversarial rewards, which is a machine learning technique.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper's approach to improving the stability of GAN training can be considered an AI technique.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper's use of neural networks in the GAN framework falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.SD (Sound): This sub-category is less likely, but the acronym "ARAML" could also refer to "Audio Random Access Markup Language". However, given the content of the abstract, it is more likely that the paper belongs to the other sub-categories listed above.
